Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?[DOSKUTSU]=20sdl3-mixer:=20Pixtone=20Mix=5FPlay?=
 =?UTF-8?q?Channel=20=E2=86=92=20MIX=5FTrack=20pool=20(64-pre-alloc)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Migrates Pixtone's SFX playback from SDL2_mixer's "channel" model
(Mix_AllocateChannels(64) + Mix_PlayChannel(chan_or_-1, chunk, loops)
+ Mix_HaltChannel + Mix_ChannelFinished) to SDL3_mixer's MIX_Track
model with a pre-allocated pool of 64 tracks.

Architectural design:
- Pre-allocate PIXTONE_TRACK_POOL_SIZE (= 64) MIX_Tracks at Pixtone::init()
  via MIX_CreateTrack against SoundManager's mixer. Mirrors the upstream
  Mix_AllocateChannels(64) call exactly. Track lifetime = Pixtone instance
  lifetime; explicitly destroyed in Pixtone::shutdown() before the mixer
  is destroyed by SoundManager::shutdown().
- The pool index doubles as the "channel id" returned by play() and
  passed back to stop(). Existing _sound_fx[].channel and _slots[64]
  bookkeeping is preserved; only the underlying handle changes from
  SDL2_mixer's opaque channel to a MIX_Track* in our pool.
- Free-track scan via _findFreeTrack() (linear over 64 entries; using
  MIX_TrackPlaying as the busy-test) replaces SDL2_mixer's implicit
  Mix_PlayChannel(-1, ...) "first free" semantics. Linear scan is fast
  enough that O(1) bookkeeping isn't worth the complexity.
- nxengine-confirmed sizing: 64 mirrors upstream's safety headroom.
  Cave Story's actual peak simultaneous SFX is ~20-30. Per-pool-slot
  MIX_Track is hundreds of bytes; total ~32 KB pool, noise even at
  Tier 3 (8 MB). Phase 9 perf work owns any future trim with profile data.

API mapping:
- Mix_QuickLoad_RAW(buf, len)        → MIX_LoadRawAudioNoCopy(mixer, buf,
                                        len, &spec, free_when_done=true)
                                        — preserves SDL2_mixer's QuickLoad
                                        ownership semantics (mixer owns
                                        the SDL_malloc'd buf, frees it on
                                        MIX_DestroyAudio).
- Mix_PlayChannel(chan, chunk, loop) → _findFreeTrack() (when chan==-1) +
                                        MIX_StopTrack(track, 0) +
                                        MIX_SetTrackAudio(track, audio) +
                                        MIX_SetTrackLoops(track, loop) +
                                        MIX_PlayTrack(track, 0).
- Mix_HaltChannel(chan)              → MIX_StopTrack(_track_pool[chan], 0).
- Mix_FreeChunk(chunk)               → MIX_DestroyAudio(audio). Removed
                                        the manual SDL_free(chunk->abuf)
                                        — NoCopy-mode buffer ownership
                                        is handed to MIX_Audio.
- Mix_ChannelFinished(global_cb)     → MIX_SetTrackStoppedCallback per-track
                                        at init, with userdata = pool
                                        index packed as (intptr_t).

Type changes (in src/sound/Pixtone.h):
- Mix_Chunk *chunk          →  MIX_Audio *chunk
- Mix_Chunk *resampled[16]  →  MIX_Audio *resampled[16]
- Added MIX_Track *_track_pool[64] = {NULL} private member.
- Added int _findFreeTrack() private method.
- Added PIXTONE_TRACK_POOL_SIZE = 64 macro.

Callback signature change (mySfxCallback):
- SDL2_mixer Mix_ChannelFinished's    void (*)(int chan)
- SDL3_mixer MIX_TrackStoppedCallback: void (*)(void *userdata, MIX_Track *track)
Implementation unpacks the pool index from userdata
((int)(intptr_t)userdata) and dispatches to the existing sfxCallback —
the std::function-based downstream hook (Pixtone::pxtSoundDone) is
unchanged.

Side fix in Pixtone::shutdown(): upstream's resampled-buffer cleanup
loop had a typo where the inner `for (int i = ...; ...; i++)` shadowed
the outer slot-iterator `i`. Result: resampled[] was leaked for slots
16..NUM_SOUNDS, and slots 0..15's resampled buffers were considered
out-of-place. Renamed inner loop variable to `j` to access
_sound_fx[i].resampled[j] correctly. The bug was harmless on SDL2_mixer
(Mix_FreeChunk on null was a no-op after the first cleanup pass), but
in SDL3_mixer territory the equivalent could surface as MIX_DestroyAudio
on a stale pointer — fixed defensively while we're rewriting these
exact lines anyway.

Patch 4/5 of the audio refactor's remaining work; only 0015 (Organya
HookMusic→TrackRawCallback + S16→float boundary) remains. Together with
0017 (foundation), 0013 (Pixtone CVT), 0016 (Ogg), and 0014 (this), the
0013-0017 series produces a compiling tree that passes the title-screen
milestone gate.
